==Further reading==
* Adam-Smith, Patsy. &quot;The Anzacs&quot; (Melbourne: Nelson, 1978).
* Beaumont, Joan. &quot;Australian military historiography.&quot; &quot;War &amp; Society&quot; 42.1 (2023): 99-121.
*Coulthard-Clark, Chris. &quot;The Third Brother: The Royal Australian Air Force, 1921–1939&quot; (Sydney: Allen &amp; Unwin in association with the RAAF, 1991)
* Gammage, Bill. &quot;The Broken Years: Australian Soldiers in the Great War&quot; (Canberra: Australian National University Press, 1974).
* Grant, Lachlan. &quot;Australian Soldiers in Asia-Pacific in World War II&quot; (Sydney: NewSouth, 2014).
* Horner, D. M. &quot;Crisis of Command: Australian Generalship and the Japanese Threat, 1941–1943&quot; (Canberra: Australian National University Press, 1978)
* Horner, D. M. &quot;High Command: Australia’s Struggle for an Independent War Strategy 1939–1945&quot; (St Leonards: Allen &amp; Unwin, 1982)
* Horner, D. M. &quot;The Gunners: A History of Australian Artillery&quot; (Sydney: Allen &amp; Unwin, 1998)
* Johnston, Mark. &quot;Anzacs in the Middle East (Melbourne: Cambridge University Press, 2013); 
* Lax, Mark. &quot;Taking the Lead: The Royal Australian Air Force, 1972–1996&quot; (Newport: Big Sky Publishing, 2020).
* Robson, L. L. &quot;The First A.I.F.: A Study of Its Recruitment 1914–1918 (Carlton: Melbourne University Press, 1970)
* Robson, L. L. &quot;The Origin and Character of the First AIF,&quot; &quot;Historical Studies&quot;, 15.61 (1973), 737–49.
* Ross, Andrew T. &quot;Armed and Ready: The Industrial Development and Defence of Australia 1900–1945&quot; (Wahroonga: Turton &amp; Armstrong), 1995.
* Stephens, Alan. &quot;Going Solo: The Royal Australian Air Force, 1946–1971&quot; (Canberra: AGPS Press, 1995)
* Stevens, David. &quot;In All Respects Ready: Australia’s Navy in World War One&quot; (South Melbourne: Oxford University Press, 2014); 
* Stevens, David ed. &quot;The Royal Australian Navy in World War IISydney: Allen &amp; Unwin, 1996).
* Thomson, Alistair. &quot;Anzac Memories: Living with the Legend&quot; (Melbourne: Oxford University Press, 1994)

