<text>Spencer Bayles is the front-man and songwriter for Leeds, England-based acoustic band Last Night&#x27;s TV. He was once a Guinness world record holder for having the longest appendix ever removed, at a staggering 21 cm (8.26 inches) long. The record is currently held by Safranco August [26 cm (10.24 in)] in 2006 during an autopsy.

